flowRoot.flowPara: Romain Reuillon et al, OpenMOLE, a workflow engine specifically tailored for the distributed exploration of simulation models, Future Generation Computer Systems, vol 29, num 8, pp. 1981-1990, 2013.
the source code and the bug tracker (www.openmole.org)

OpenMOLE is developped by the Complex Systems community. It relies on the 4 pilars of the open-source movement, meaning that the code can freely be executed, studied, modified and redistributed. This choice is part of the open science trend that we defend and which promotes the sharing and the reusabilty of code in scientific publications.
As it is usually the case in the open-source movement, OpenMOLE invites anyone to contribute to the project by:
proposing helpful enhancements or use cases (shared with the community on the website),
the "Institut des Systmes Complexes - Paris le-de-France"
Already used in various scientific fields
